The system went live on Monday following a week-long delay due to legal threats over the department’s amended admissions policy. JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Department of Education says it's received almost 300,000 online applications for 2020. The system went live on Monday following a week-long delay due to legal threats over the department’s amended admissions policy. READ: Online school applications system officially live The department says there have been some technical difficulties. Among them are some parents who have not received the correct reference numbers. READ: Date set for online applications for Grade 1 to 8 The department says these issues are being addressed. Applications for admissions for grades 1 and 8 will close at midnight on the 22nd of July.